{
  "text": "Several million CAGE tags were produced by us from a wide range of tissues and conditions of human and mouse in the transition between the FANTOM3 and the FANTOM4 project [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Re-mapping all of these data to the same genome assemblies used in FANTOM4 (hg18 for human and mm9 for mouse) lead us to the finding that retrotransposon transcription substantially regulates the transcriptional output of the mammalian genome [CITATION_3] . We consistently aggregated all data into CAGE tag cluster, a unit of CAGE tags overlapping on the genome [CITATION_4] , by this facilitate the access to one of the largest resources of TSSs. We additionally provide the converted coordinates of FANTOM3 tag cluster data (26) to enable comparison to our earlier results.",
